Cell.Data: This spreadsheet is used to support the definition of resources or data types (structures). A complete set of instructions on the various tabs, columns and rules associated with populating this spreadsheet can be found here:
This represents the Medicinal Product as authorised by a Medicines Regulatory Agency in a region and has the following attributes
The MPID for the Medicinal Product, which shall be always specified. It is specified as text

The combined pharmaceutical dose form is a single term to describe two or more manufactured items that are intended to be combined in a specific way to produce a single pharmaceutical product. It includes information on the manufactured dose form of each manufactured item and the administrable dose form of the pharmaceutical product. If the Medicinal Product requires description of a combined pharmaceutical dose form, it can be specified here using a term and a term identifier as defined in ISO 11239 and the resulting terminology

If the Medicinal Product is subject to additional mnitoring, this can be specified using an appropriate controlled vocabulary. The controlled term and the controlled term identifier shall be specified

If the Medicinal Product is subject to specific special measures, these can be specified using an appropriate controlled vocabulary. The controlled term and the controlled term identifier shall be specified
Indicates if the Medicinal Product is also authorised for use in children
The description if the medicinal product is subject to orphan designation and intended for the treatment of a rare disease
The packaged version(s) of the Medicinal Product
The phramaceutical product aspects of the Medicinal Product
The clinical particulars for the Medicinal Product
Any document(s) officially submitted to a medicines regulatory agency shall be specified as a regulated document
The reference to the regulatory decision document related to the granting of the authorisation or the latest update of the regulated product information shall be specified in text

The date corresponding to a version of a regulated document containing regulated medicinal product information (e.g. elements related to the Summary of Product Characteristics, product labelling). A complete date consisting of day, month and year shall be specified using the ISO 8601 date format. NOTE: Document version date corresponds to the tracking versions of a regulated document. It does not correspond to the actual revisions or regulatory timelines that may be captured within a regulated document
The type of document that is supporting a version increment shall be specified using an appropriate controlled vocabulary. The controlled term and the controlled term identifier shall be specified
The actual document that is supporting a version increment shall be attached. The format of the document attachment shall be specified by regional implementations
This attribute defines the language used for the information related to the regulatory submission
This attribute is used to define the graphic media type of the attached document
A number identifying a specific version of the attached regulatory document
A number used to group together a set of specific versions of the same regulatory document

The characteristics of an authorised medicinal product as defined in this International Standard shall be versioned within a regulated document, as applicable. For a given version, some characteristics of the medicinal product have changed but are not different to a sufficient extent to warrant the assignment of a new primary identifier as specified in the Identifying Characteristics for Authorised Medicinal Products section within this International Standard. However, the difference(s) are required to be recorded and tracked against the MPID/PCID
This attribute is for the unique code identifying the regulatory information submission

The date specified in the regulatory decision document by which the authorisation or the updates to the regulated product information become effective shall be specified. A complete point in time date consisting of day, month and year shall be specified using the ISO 8601 date format
This attribute defines the language used for the information related to the regulatory submission
A number identifying a specific version of the regulatory information submission
A number used to group together a set of specific versions of the regulatory information submission
This class is used to identify any type of master file related to the medicinal product, for instance Pharmacovigilance System Master File
This attribute is to define which kind of master file is indicated
This attribute is for a code to uniquely identify a master file

A set of classes that are used to describe the custodian organisation of the master file and the location where the master file is located. Please use the same set of classes as used for describing Organisations
The unique identifier of the organisation shall be provided. An international coding system for unique organisation identifiers can be used
The name of the organisation shall be provided in text
The address of the organisation shall be provided using a standardised structured address format. The format is specified in ISO/TS 20443
The confidentiality level of the organisation information can be specified using an appropriate controlled vocabulary. The controlled term and a term identifier shall be specified
These are coordinates that identify precisely the location where the organisation is set. Please see ISO/TS 20443 for more information and example
The Medicinal Product Name, represented in one or more languages, is one of the defining characteristics of a Medicinal Product and its MPID
The full and complete Medicinal Product Name as approved by the Medicines Regulatory Agency in a regions shall be specified, as text
The invented name (i.e. trade name) of the Medicinal Product without the trademark or any other similar designations reflected in the Medicinal Product Name can be specified as text, where applicable
The scientific or common (i.e. generic) name of the Medicinal Product without any other descriptors can be specified as text, where applicable
The strength, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable. This strength name part can differ from the concept of product strength itself

The pharmaceutical dose form, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable. This pharmaceutical dose form name part can differ from the concept of administrable dose form and manufactured dose form as described in ISO / TS 20443
The formulation, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable
The intended use, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable
The target population, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable
The container or pack, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable
The device, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable
The trademark, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable
The time/period, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable
The flavour, if reflected in the Medicinal Product Name, can be specified as text, where applicable
A delimiter separates one composite in a segment from another, or separates one sub-composite from another
The country and optionally the region where the Medicinal Product Name of a Medicinal Product is authorised shall be specified in the official language as applicable
The country where the Medicinal Product Name is applicable shall be described using ISO 3166 1 alpha-2 code elements

The jurisdiction within the country where the Medicinal Product Name is applicable can be described using an appropriate controlled vocabulary, if appropriate. Thecontrolled term and the controlled term identifier shall be specified

The language of the Medicinal Product Name as applicable in the specified country and jurisdiction if appropriate shall be specified using ISO 639-1 (Codes for the representation of names of languages)
This class includes several attributes required to have all the information related to a product with an orphan designation status
This attribute is for the type of intended use of the medicinal product, for instance disease prevention, treatment or diagnostic
This attribute is the procedure number for the orphan designation authorisation application
This attribute is for describing the status of the Orphan Designation authorisation, for instance granted, pending, expired or withdrawn
This attribute is for the date in which the orphan designation status was granted
This field is to indicate the orphan designation decision number

The Medicinal Product can be classified according to various classification systems, which may be regional or international. One or more of these various classifications of the product can be specified in this section
The individual value from the classification system that applies to the Medicinal Product shall be specified using a controlled term and a controlled term identifier

There can be a cross-reference between the MPIDs/PCIDs of the authorised medicinal product(s) and the related IMPIDs/IPCIDs of an investigational medicinal product(s) assigned during the development phase and clinical investigation of that medicinal product. In addition, there may be references between authorised medicinal products and there corresponding identifiers. The related medicinal products, and investigational medicinal products can be specified with their corresponding identifiers
Used to reference other IMPID(s) or MPID(s) related to the medicinal. Please see more information and examples on the use of this attribute in ISO/TS 20443
To identify which kind of medicinal product is cross-referenced. Please see more information and examples on the use of this attribute in ISO/TS 20443
